s in the UK, Japan, Australia, Brazil, Canada, Portugal, Sweden and The Netherlands. Leading academics examine issues including the interface of HSWs with the health professions, regulatory practice risks, employment challenges and the dilemmas of an ageing population. Crucial future policy recommendations are also made for a world becoming increasingly dependent on HSWs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aAllied health personnel. 7aMEDICAL / Health Care Delivery.2bisacsh1 aAllsop, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlmeida, Joana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarros, Nelson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerta, Whitney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDass, Adrian Rohit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeber, Raisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDent, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunér, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHosoda, Miwako, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaporte, Audrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeemeijer, Aukje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiljegren, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLum, Janet M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNancarrow, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoordegraaf, Mirko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlin, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaks, Mike, econt